woke up a bit ago. was hoping for something in the microwave for me to eat but nothing, so i have to go out and get some chicken. gonna go to popeyes again
ive had like 5 or 4 of the same meal from that place since first eating there a couple days ago.
which is normal, its always what happens when i finally get the courage to eat at somewhere new and it turns out that its good. because i get so sick of eating everything else i do by that point that its impossible for me to have any of them while theres another choice.
its a nice little grace period whenever it happens, i think, but the catch is that soon im probably going to grow just as jaded with popeyes as i am with everything else i know. not because its gonna get worse, but its just what happens when you eat the same thing over and over again for however long, it can be as good as it wants but youll start holding some contempt for it anyway.
but anyway, i guess thats not really worth thinking about then. right now i enjoy it and thats what matters, and its giving me the motivation to get some fresh air, so thats always nice. especially since its the evening and all.
im gonna see if theres any sour gummies in the market on my way back. ive been wanting something properly sour for a long time now, but its just that everything i pick up from nearby stores suck.
the sour gum that was sold here, it used to be great. in middle school i got a lot and stashed them away cause i was addicted to them. it was perfectly sour, really all i can say about it. one time i bought a hundred of them and brought the bag to school for some reason so the teacher took it away. imagine taking away some sour gum from a kid, god how much of a fucking loser do you have to be
anyway, today theyve declined. the same brand of sour gum is a joke now, it barely makes you feel anything. ill have to look for something that looks okay on a bigger market.
have been waiting for my phone to charge, and its probably got enough in it now.

posts.name: Madokano
posts.com:
was a nice meal. i really wish i could manifest one of those things with my thoughts at any time, because that chicken would make for the perfect late-night food. apparently you get to order food at any time of the day you want in the US. imagine thinking you suffer when living there, wow. id kill to be able to do that
what makes eating out possible for me is being able to watch a game dungeon episode or whatever with earphones on, i dont think id ever wanna do it otherwise, itd just feel boring. in general i cant eat without having something to watch or listen to, which i think is a pretty common thing with people nowadays. i dont see anything really wrong with it
probably never going to eat with anyone else again for the rest of my life, or at least not voluntarily. ive been brought along onto meals a few times by classmates and it always felt uncomfortable for me. im too self-conscious while eating around others, that ill look weird or something by not eating in a certain way.
and thats not just placebo, i think im aware that i eat clumsily. ive even been told so once on those occasions that i ate with people, that im embarrassing them somehow lol. i didnt really get how then and neither now. but ig that tells me enough.
it doesnt bother me at all when im eating by myself cause i could give less of a shit as long as i enjoy what im having, but when theres others around, yeah, i get pressure which leads to me being even clumsier. ironically the more self-conscious and overly careful of what im doing, the more im likely to mess it up
theres also that i cant really enjoy my meal properly if theres anybody around. it can be some incredibly good food, but i wont really be paying attention to that because of all the dumb things going through my mind. ill just perceive it in the back of my mind rather than taking all of it in, i dont know if thats a good way to word it but yeah.
anyway idk why i went on about that. charlim

posts.name: Madokano
posts.com:
catch is that it was pricey this time. i asked for a bucket of fries to take home so i can eat it later at night, and turns out that it costs more than a fair bit. not really a worrisome amount, but just a "well i wont be getting this every day" kind of cost.
not really my fault, surprisingly. when i ordered the same thing online it was about half the price, but for some reason when you buy it in person its more. curious that
but whatever. i still got my bucket of fries, and thats pretty cool. the next time i eat there i might just not ask for fries to have alongside the chicken but only to take home, the cost would probably be less then.
actually, i wonder if they would let me only buy some fries. hm. if so, i would get some every day after school, and thatd just be the best thing. but the hard part is going to be going up to them and asking "hey could you let me just have a bucket of fries" because if i get told no i would feel really dumb. i guess ill just slip in the question the next time im getting the usual.
anyhow, i have an urge to eat them all right now, but i need to save them up for later in the night cause i think my friends are gonna be online. i wanna have fries to snack on as im bullshitting thats more fun. i guess ill go grab a couple now though, wouldnt hurt alongside some tea.
oh, and i didnt get anything sour on the way back. its not that i forgot, its that i get this feeling of urgency whenever im in a store. i cant stick around too long to look at stuff and see if theres anything i want, because i just feel compelled to get whatever i came there to get and go. just that feeling of eyes on you, idk.
i doubt there was anything from the glimpse i got at the candy section, anyway. is the sour market really dead? cant give up already, ill give it another try sometime.

i really have no idea what the cause for the issue is. its not like my laptop is so bad that it cant run cs:s, i can run pretty much any other source game just fine, or well at least much better than cs:s. and cs:s isnt really anything that pushes source to its limits or anything, its pretty barebones. if you can run half life 2 you should be able to run cs:s.

climb is good for me still because of how relaxing it is. turning my brain off with something nice in the background as i casually try to do the jumps, idk its just really nice, and it also has a lot to do with the map itself, some just have nice scenery which makes it really comfy (its a gay word but im using it whatever) to play in.

posts.name: Madokano
posts.com:
you move too fast and have to pay more attention in bhop/surf, so you dont get to take that kind of stuff in. with climb its only as fast-paced as you want it to be no matter how hard the map is, so you get to chill and take it slow. the ideal map is one thats not really hard and has a nice environment, all things ticked then i have a nice hour or so of serenity on my hands. its sort of like walking around an atmospheric map in gmod, but with the extra of it being a movement gamemode, so idk thats really nice to me. if i was any competent with mapping in source id love to make something perfect to what i have in mind. maybe one day
that being said i havent played it much, because again cs:s is just annoying with its performance. even in these maps sometimes i drop down to below 20 fps and although i dont mind it much, after spending your entire life playing on a craptop you dont get bothered by shitty performance in games anymore, it still makes you feel annoyed with it when u mess up the same easy ass jump for the millionth time cause your mouse feels like its on ice. cause that makes you really inconsistent, you can do one jump however many times you want and youll still mess it up eventually because you cant really get used to how frame spikes affect what ur doing. sucks to mess something up without it being your fault
and i dont really like using noclip to get back on the platform i fell from, so i always start over on a climb. because of that at some point it can get tedious instead of relaxing, lol. but its okay, thats still thats a part of it.
anyway yeah. apparently cs:s is 5 gigs, not 2. still pretty small. i also have to look for a map to play on, cause i dont feel like repeating the ones i played. if i cant find anything that looks nice enough then whatever. ill only bother to redownload the game if i do
theres also playing easier jump maps in tf2 for a similar experience, but eh i dont get the same feel from it. i like cs:s for its barebones source look.

looks pretty nice. i really like greeny maps that look like theyre part of nature, they give me the same feeling as that one windows xp wallpaper. its the kind of place that i would wanna be at in real life really.
its also cool when you turn around and theres the flat source skybox that the mapmaker didnt bother to replace with anything or the random shit they decided to put around, it makes the place feel dreamy so its not quite natural still.

another thing i like about climb maps is u get to see your destination, if that makes sense. you see the high up place that you have to get up all the way to and it feels distant at the start, and then when you finally get up there and you look back down where u came from it feels nice, like u accomplished something lol. i bet someone who hikes in real life would be able to tell you the feeling. getting through things is naturally satisfying but it being in front of your eyes is better because you get to perceive and comprehend it, you know? just a "wow i was there and now im here this is cool"
thats a thing bhop or surf maps dont have much of, you just dont get to look back and see all the shit you had to pass through to get where u are because you get teleported away most of the time, and also that those tend to be more fast-paced. here you can stop and look around or down where you came from at any time.
some bhop maps are one big area with no teleports, but you still dont get to look at where you came from all that well because theres not much verticality to them.
its a small thing and nobody who plays the maps seriously would care yeah, but when youre playing for the sake of relaxing, getting to look around and take things in is really good.
oh and i forgot to mention before. another reason i dont wanna bother playing bhop/surf is cause they need you having the right configuration and yada yada to play offline, at least here you can just load the map and play. much better imo

been feeling like playing through half life 2 for some reason. ive actually never done it. the only half life games ive played through were blue shift and opposing force, not even the original cause i dont know, it always just came off as boring to me. for its time it mustve been a really good game, sure, but to me half life 1 feels too sluggish to play. i just dont really like the combat in it, i guess. its not like i dislike games from that era, ive played quake 1 a lot, and thats a great game to compare it to, actually. i like the movement and combat in quake a lot but when it comes to half life things feel slow and more tedious. im sure thats the intent they were after, to make a bit of a slower and more tactical game rather than jumping around and shooting everything (even if thats what people end up doing in half life 1 anyway) but its not really refined enough for me to prefer it over anything else. primarily i just dont like how weak the weapons feel, no matter what i use in goldsrc it feels like im holding a peashooter, pump 4 meatshots into someones chest with a shotgun and they dont die, idk, i never enjoyed how it felt. and it hasnt been too long since i last experienced it, a while ago i played through some campaigns on sven coop with buddies and yeah, i really didnt like the feel of the game then neither. not that i hated it, but nothing i would boot up and play. even if i was in the nineties when half life 1 first came out id play quake over it instead i think, lol. im in the group that thinks half life is overrated, basically.

posts.name: Madokano
posts.com:
>>16892927
thats not really saying much, though. because to me the half life games arent really important, its the engines theyre on that are. theyre okay as games with all the cool thinking put into them, sure, but i think that if they were on anything other than engines valve made then they really wouldnt be remembered to be much of a big deal, people kinda ignore that and just say "wow half life is the most important game ever" whilst eh, not really, its source that was so important, half life was always just a tool for it
half life 2 to me comes as basically just a showcase of what the source engine can do, like a tech demo except its a full game. its a solid game but pretty much everything that makes it that good is what the source engine is. 90% of its memorability just comes off from that, and also ig how revolutionary it was for its time.
the people who say they find half life 2 stale nowadays despite recognizing it as good, its probably because weve just gotten very used to tech like source's being in games. it doesnt come off as insanely impressive anymore cause youve seen flashier stuff in newer releases, u go back and look at half life now ya its cool stuff but its not really innovative to your eyes
on the other hand people back in the day played through half life 2 thinking its the coolest shit cause thats how advanced source was for its time, they were seeing stuff not really done before and it was all tied to the half life name. thats why all the talk of it gets tied into half life rather than the source engine
maybe im not making any sense with my point but idk thats always what i thought.
this is the same reason ive been wanting to play through half life 2 though
to me its a very chill game cause its just a series of showcases of what the source engine is capable of lol
since im so used to source that its as familiar to me as fucking real life at this point, itd be like taking a walk

ended up playing cs:s. but not climb, not at the start. i actually played the real game for a bit. thats cause i pretty much confirmed that you do need to be on a server with the right plugins after all for a bunch of climb maps, not every single one but still. played a map that did need it and its annoying to have to skip some jumps cause of it, and so i figured eh ill hop onto an actual server fuck it why not.
surprisingly it ran fine, or well just what i consider fine at least. like 40 or a little so fps with constant stutters on a full dust 2 deathmatch server. not ideal but playable. i realized that i could lower down the directx version down to 8 because you can do that with every source game afaik, so doing that gave me a really nice fps boost. probably the single most fps giving thing u can do for any valve game. the catch is that it makes the game a bit more unstable, visuals get a bit fucky in some maps and ull probably crash more. but not really anything to worry about. i wish that every source game let u use an fps config like tf2 lets you do, i never really understood why it was only on that game. the only idea i have is because of valve not wanting their games to look ugly when people stream them or show in videos, but back in the way when cs:s released that wasnt really a thing in their minds, only around the era where they raped cs:go's artstyle and turned it into a candyland game i think is when they started doing that. if they just let you use an fps config on cs:s id be a much happier person, but oh well. ill take what i can get.
oh, and i also had to change some of the settings on high to get the most fps i can, because in source low and high settings change whether your gpu or cpu gets the most load, so you have to adjust it to whichever one is better. weird shit
the bigger problem was ping but ill get to that

posts.name: Madokano
posts.com:
first, wow, i forgot how good cs:s felt to play. the last time i played it is probably close to a decade ago, and even then i pretty much only hanged out on bhop servers, so i had entirely forgotten how it feels to shoot shit in it. i had a little bit of an idea from watching videos of it now and then, but ya u cant really know until youve played it for yourself
its soooooo much better than both csgo and 1.6, honestly. the guns feel punchy as hell to shoot, the movement is fluid and fights just plays out better than any other cs ive played. getting kills is also more satisfying and overall everything is nicer idk. i dont know if i can think of a single overall improvement csgo has over css, maybe the ui? but honestly not even that lol, i never really liked the round weapon buy menu in csgo, always preferred the classic one. even the look of cs:s is much prettier, cant even give it the graphics medal.
one thing i rly like is ragdolls. ya it sounds like a small and dumb thing and it kinda is but still. i love how bodies flop when you kill people in css or how they fly away if a grenade blows them up, you headshot a guy whos running over to you and his body will basically fly over to your direction, its just cool to see after u kill people. in cs:go all the ragdolls are just fucking sandbags or some shit and drop down in place no matter what happens, even a grenade exploding right under you feet barely sends you in the air. i can meatshot someone in css and watch their body fly and do half a flip, thats just really cool.
the guns, at least the automatic ones, arent that much different from csgo on how i felt except maybe more inaccurate over distance, but thats probably just me sucking at the game. but they still manage to be better imo, because the feel is superior. the sounds are nicer, the animations are rly good imo, i love how your gun sways around as you move your mouse, that doesnt happen at all in csgo which sucks, and ya its just more fun to shoot

posts.name: Madokano
posts.com:
but what i rly liked were the shotguns, i tried them out and then it was just all i played with for like an hour. it feels soooo good to get meatshots, people tend to die instantly and shotguns actually work like shotguns meaning if there are two people really close to each other one blast is going to do a fuckton of damage to both. throughout that one hour of playtime i got like 3 occasions where i killed 2 people with one shot. that just feels really good when it happens and i wish more games tried to make their shotguns be able to do that, in a lot of them its rare that you get to damage more than one guy with ur shot even if theyre standing right next to each other. they need to be literally inside of each other in most games for it to work properly
it pretty much nails perfectly how a shotgun in a game should feel when youre shooting at people 5 or so meters in front of you, they fucking die and it feels satisfying. along with the cool animation and sound design and yada yada i rly enjoyed clicking on people.
besides that though they also got down the shooting at people far away part right. pellets dont disappear into the void after traveling more than 10 meters, if you place your crosshair well enough you can still get two shot kills on people fairly far away from u while using a shotty, and thats also how it supposed to be. its not so accurate that you can just run and lazily aim then get ur kill, you have to stand still and make sure ur aiming at the right spot, and that makes it balanced enough. in other cs games the shotguns just simply arent as satisfying, i remember i used them a lot in csgo when i was little and although they had their moments it still just sucked and felt weak, and in cs 1.6 i dont even remember lol i dont think anyone used shotguns in that game
they probably nerfed shotguns to make them more fun to play against, but in return theyre just not fun to use, so, eh.

anyway ya it was fun until it got boring, rushing to the same spot over and over and shooting at the same retards does get old after a bit, no matter how good the gunplay is. but it was mainly because of the ping, i wouldve kept playing for a little while longer otherwise. i guess it was some south american server and i had like 200 ping so it was just cancer to get in fights, everytime you get shot with high ping the game freaks out not knowing where to place you, so you jitter around and get shot through walls as youre running even though in your vision whoever shot u isnt even in sight, yada yada its just a bad experience. im okay with playing with low fps but high ping is annoying, which is actually the opposite of how i feel with games usually, but in css having high ping is even more annoying cause you move rather slow, so it makes ur movement kind of tanky. id rather not deal with it

so whatever after looking through a bunch of servers and all of them being bots i gave up. the game was starting to leak memory and run even more like shit anyway
figured after that i should see if theres any climb servers on the browser, and turns out theres one left still. its not a very popular gamemode and i think the people that do play it are on csgo instead, so lucky that anybody is bothering to run a server for it here.
anyway, after changing my settings so that i dont have to download 900 different models of hatsune miku i got in and it was pretty nice. being able to set checkpoints instead of noclipping every time you fail a jump is already a lifechanger.
i couldnt really tell if there was a difference in the movement from a default server, but i guess if there is its stuff you have to look hard enough for.
it turns out that a couple of shit that i thought u need a plugin for were kinda just me being bad, like a trick where you have to almost fully crouch first then jump to get extra height. that was really weird to me, ive never seen it in any other source game before. tf2 has c-tapping but its not really the same.
and no this isnt crouch jumping, not exactly. thats why i was confused by it. only figured it out by random experimenting.
either way, its still definitely better to play on a server just because of being able to set checkpoints.
plus i get to play on a brand new map with just a command instead of having to go look for and download one, so thats always nice too. its good when you have servers to yourself so u can switch maps as much as you want
